[
  "John P. McConnell is the executive chairman at Worthington Industries, a Columbus, Ohio-based steel processor and producer.",
  "He stepped down as CEO in September 2020, after leading the company for 27 years.",
  "Worthington Industries was founded in 1955 by McConnell's father John H. McConnell (d. 2008). ",
  " He's the majority owner of the NHL's Columbus Blue Jackets, a team started by his father in 2000.",
  "McConnell started his career in 1975 as a general laborer in a Worthington steel plant in Louisville, Kentucky. "
]